-- Greece May Cut Tourism Tax, Airport Fees, Naftemporiki Reports
-- B y   T o m   S t o u k a s
-- 2012-07-13T06:54:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-13/greece-may-cut-tourism-tax-airport-fees-naftemporiki-reports.html
Greece may cut value added tax for
the  tourism industry  and is examining airport fees, to make the
industry more competitive,  Naftemporiki  reported, citing an
interview with Tourism Minister Olga Kefalogianni.  The climate for Greek tourism has improved greatly since
the coalition government was formed last month, Kefalogianni
told the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tom Stoukas in Athens at 
